[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{The chances of a slam on this hand are very small, and if EAST decides to use RKCB it will 
just confuse matters when WEST shows two Key Cards.

EAST has a better way to find out about the hand. She bids 2NT asking WEST to further describe 
his hand. WEST should then bid 3NT, showing a solid suit headed by AKQ.

WEST cannot have as much as an extra Jack, so EAST just passes 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
