[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH realizes NORTH has fewer than 8 points, but the 3\S support bid is enough 
for her to try a RKCB 4NT bid.

NORTH shows two Key Cards and SOUTH figures they will be the \SK and one of the 
red Aces. So she bids 6\S. If instead the Key Cards are the two red Aces SOUTH 
might possibly make all thirteen tricks with a finesse.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
